eter Ustinov]], <!--Bach with Ljubimov,--> by [[Kurt Weill]], with [[Milva]] singing, and music by [[Aldo Clementi]], [[Azio Corghi]] and [[Franco Donatoni]], among others. He conducted one Verdi opera at La Scala, ''[[Luisa Miller]]'' in 1989, with [[Katia Ricciarelli]] in the title role.<ref name=\"Scala\" />\n\nPesk\u00f3 was [[Generalmusikdirektor]] of the [[Deutsche Oper am Rhein]] from 1996 to 1999.<ref name=\"Who\" /> He served as chief conductor of the {{ill|Orquestra Sinf\u00f3nica Portuguesa|pt}}, the orchestra of the [[Teatro Nacional de S\u00e3o Carlos]] in Lisbon, from 2001 to 2004.<ref name=\"WZ\" /> He was chief conductor of the [[Pannon Philharmonic]] in [[P\u00e9cs]] from 2009 to 2011. In 2012, he suffered a stroke which left him unable to continue conducting.<ref name=\"WZ\" />\n\nHe made many recordings,<ref>{{AllMusic|id=mn0001646354}}</ref> and lectured at the [[Musikhochschule Berlin]].<ref name=\"Who\" />\n\nPesk\u00f3 died in Budapest on 31 March 2020 at age of 83.<ref name=\"Scala\" /><ref name=\"WZ\" /><ref>[https://fidelio.hu/klasszikus/elhunyt-pesko-zoltan-vilaghiru-magyar-karmester-154174.html Elhunyt Pesk\u00f3 Zolt\u00e1n vil\u00e1gh\u00edr\u0171 magyar karmester] {{in lang|hu}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist\n| refs =\n\n<ref name=\"Scala\">{{cite web\n| url = https://www.connessiallopera.it/news/2020/zoltan-pesko-il-teatro-alla-scala-ricorda-il-direttore-scomparso/\n| title = Zolt\u00e1n Pesk\u00f3: il Teatro alla Scala ricorda il direttore scomparso\n| website = [[La Scala]]\n| date = 1 April 2020\n| language = it\n| accessdate = 2 April 2020\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Who\">{{cite web\n| url = http://www.whoswho.de/bio/zoltn-pesk.html\n| title = Zolt\u00e1n Pesk\u00f3\n| website = whoswho.de\n| date = \n| language = de\n| accessdate = 2 April 2020\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"WZ\">{{cite news\n| url = https://www.wienerzeitung.at/nachrichten/kultur/klassik/2056274-Dirigent-Zoltan-Pesko-gestorben.html\n| title = Dirigent Zoltan Pesko 